<br>
Disregarding TOA (which I worry about in this vein), there are simply not enough situations where anybody would want this ability. I guess swimming super-fast could be a great tool for getting out of trouble, so long as:<br>
<br>
You're near water.<br>
You resist the root/crippling poison/Instamez<br>
You can swim out of range of danger before you're dead.<br>
<br>
The fast that this RA is a scaling thing, ie MOW1, 2, 3, makes it even less popular, and the bonus in swim-speed is also extremely insignificant.<br>
<br>
Regarded by many as the worst RA in the game. ^<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Whirling Dervish</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Seeing as DW% is randomly generated, this 3% -per-level DW% improvement is severely lacking. The RA, even at high levels, will not stay active for long enough to see results. Our offhand is also the weakest part of our offense, and if we're styling, all we're getting is more offhand hits. Compare this to LA which swings both hands every time, and is free.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Mastery of Arms</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
LOTS of people say this RA is broken. I wouldn't be surprised.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Veil Recovery</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Like MOW, this RA is gonna be useful/make a difference in very few situations, has very small benefit unless specced high etc. It's probably more useful in PvE while levelling up, but still doesn't beat Purge for 4 pts, which will remove Rez Illness instantly, every half hour. Let's hope we don't die more frequently than this!<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Prevent Flight</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
On the Root timer? You mean if a Wizard with 1 in earth tries a failed AE root, it won't work in this fight? This is a VERY expensive Realm Ability, which I would expect not to have an immunity timer. <p><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em> Would you think a man going naked with a sword is scarier than a man going naked with an axe? </em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> - Tatsumaru<br>
