<br>
Merc RA list:<br>
<br>
<br>
Aug Stats - good for filling gaps in Spec / also pre req for MoArms ( covered on MoArms ) .<br>
<br>
Long Wind - good for the extended sprint ability / usefull for PvE + RvR .<br>
<br>
Tireless - good idea but simply doesn't provide enough return value to be worth the cost imho .<br>
<br>
Regeneration - good idea but simply doesn't provide enough return value to be worth the cost imho .<br>
<br>
Toughness - well worth a few Rp's depending on RR as even at lvl 1 = 3% the bonus has a good return value per lvl of Rp's invested .<br>
<br>
Mastery of Water - hahahahahahahahaha ...no really ...you mean this wasn't a joke from the start !! ?  &gt; : P<br>
<br>
Avoidance of Magic - good for filling gaps in Spec at any RR lvl and a good return value for Rp's spent .<br>
<br>
Lifter - great return value for Rp's spent - essential for those interested in Siege warfare and for 1 Rp anyone can greatly increase their capacity to carry , benifits both RvR and PvE for equiptment - loot . <br>
<br>
Veil Recovery - hahahahahahahahaha ...no really ...you mean this wasn't a joke from the start !! ?  &gt; : P<br>
<br>
Mastery of Parry - great RA , not sure it shouldn't be made a Class ability ie : lvl 10 = 3% - lvl 20 = 6% - lvl 30 = 9% ...etc .<br>
<br>
Mastery of Arms - probably the best thought out RA imho ( broken or not ;p ) as it requires 10 Rp's for Aug St 3 which allows access to MoArms , this in turn allowed Merc's using slower spd weaps such as 4.0 + ... to lower their ******** spd , this i feel sort of puts this RA even at lvl 1 as some thing that is more likely to be found in the arsenal of a RR5-6 player more often than some one lower lvl and as such is why i thought it was a reasonably well thought out RA , since ToA ....does it have any use any more .....enquiring minds wanna know ! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
Mastery of Pain - great , smashing , super......leave it alone thnx .<br>
<br>
Dodger - good basic RA , only used it at lvl 1 so far myself but as it increases my chances to land the DW Twin Rtn / Orbit combo it's a bonus for both PvE and RvR .<br>
<br>
Dualists Reflexes - super,  smashing , great RA , not sure it shouldn't be made a Class ability ie : lvl 10 = 3% - lvl 20 = 6% - lvl 30 = 9% ...etc but if not plzzzzzz......leave it alone thnx .<br>
<br>
Determination - has it's + and - points , great for busting that mezz and still attacking ....but not if your now the ONLY moving target  ( :; ) .... works well in combo with AoMagic - Purge and PF ( for chasing down those Bards :P ) .<br>
Prevent Flight - has it's + and - points , good but expensive RA . ( see below ) .<br>
<br>
First Aid/Ignore Pain - good but expensive RA combo great for both PvE and RvR although Rp cost does usually mean most  Merc's are forced to make a choice between PF or FA-IP combo until higher RR's so there is a good overall balance when taking these 2 as an example .<br>
<br>
Trip/Grapple - great RA , not sure it shouldn't be made a Class ability ie : lvl 10 = 3% - lvl 20 = 6% - lvl 30 = 9% ...or simillar , these RA's are perfect for Merc's as front line assault but are too costly to consider at the moment for anyone below about RR8-9 would be my guess after the more essential needs for earlier game needs .<br>
<br>
Purge - great for Merc's especially at cost of 4 Rp's , would like to see it scale for Mercs into Major Purge =   +3 closest grp members -cost 7 Rp's  and Greater Purge =  Full Grp members - cost 10 Rp's .<br>
<br>
Void - hmmm , sounds good , not tried it personally ...does it do exactly what it says on the tin !! ?   ; P<br>
<br>
Second Wind - like Eldorado it glimmers on the horizon but alas that's where it stays for now .. ; /<br>
<br>
Whirling Dervish - lose it <br>
Bladedance - lose it <br>
Hail of Blows - lose it <br>
Rain of XXX - lose it <br>
Empty Mind - lose it <br>
<br>
Kerrec Snowmane , hope that helps in some small way .<br>
<br>
Agroerbert McFlurry .<br>
Alderly Edge , MLF .<br>
